If you want a **PDF merging/rearranging tool to be commercially viable**, the key is not just merging files. That feature alone is already free in many places. The real opportunity is **workflow automation and document manipulation**, especially for businesses that handle lots of PDFs (legal, engineering, accounting, construction, etc.).

Given your background running **Ace Industrial Controls**, you probably already encounter PDF workflows like:

* combining manuals
* rearranging drawings
* compiling calibration reports
* assembling project documentation

So the winning product focuses on **saving professionals time**.

Below is a structured breakdown of **features that actually create commercial value**.

---

# 1. Core PDF Manipulation (Must-Have)

These are the baseline features expected from any professional tool.

### Merge / Split

* Merge multiple PDFs
* Split by page range
* Split every N pages
* Split by bookmark
* Split by detected separator pages

### Page Reordering

* Drag-and-drop page sorting
* Rotate pages
* Delete pages
* Duplicate pages
* Extract pages into new PDF

### Page Range Logic

Allow expressions like:

```
1-5, 8, 10-20
odd pages
even pages
reverse order
```

This is surprisingly rare in simpler tools but highly useful.

---

# 2. Visual Page Organizer (Huge UX Value)

Users love a **thumbnail grid editor**.

Features:

* Zoomable page thumbnails
* Drag pages between documents
* Multi-select pages
* Batch rotate/delete
* Page labels

Think of it like **Lightroom but for PDFs**.

---

# 3. Bookmark & Table-of-Contents Tools

For large documents this is massive.

Features:

* Auto-generate bookmarks from:

  * file names
  * page headings
  * OCR text
* Merge bookmarks across documents
* Edit bookmark hierarchy
* Auto-create a clickable Table of Contents

Example workflow:

```
Combine:
Pump Manual.pdf
Electrical Drawings.pdf
Control Panel Specs.pdf

Automatically create bookmarks for each section.
```

Extremely valuable for **engineering documentation packages**.

---

# 4. OCR + Text Awareness

Most PDFs are scans.

Key features:

### OCR

* Convert scans → searchable text
* Detect page orientation

### Text-based splitting

Example:

```
Split document every time the text "Calibration Certificate" appears
```

Used heavily in:

* accounting
* shipping paperwork
* compliance documentation

---

# 5. Batch Processing / Automation

This is where **real money is made**.

Features:

### Folder Watcher

```
Watch folder → merge PDFs → output compiled file
```

### Batch Workflows

Users create recipes:

Example:

```
Input folder:
Combine all PDFs
Sort by filename
Add bookmark per file
Add cover page
Export to compiled report.pdf
```

This is **gold for office workflows**.

---

# 6. Smart Separator Detection

Used by offices scanning hundreds of documents.

Features:

Split when:

* blank page
* barcode
* QR code
* specific text
* page color change

Example:

```
Scan 200 pages
Software splits automatically into 40 invoices
```

Law firms and accounting offices use this daily.

---

